meta.name: Monday Night Football
meta.description: Monday Night Football is a live television broadcast of weekly National Football League (NFL) games on ESPN in the United States. From 1970 to 2005, it aired on sister broadcast network ABC. Monday Night Football was, along with Hallmark Hall of Fame and the Walt Disney anthology television series, one of the longest-running prime time programs ever on commercial network television, and one of the highest-rated, particularly among male viewers.

Pittsburgh Steelers at New York Giants
videos.overview: Ben Roethlisberger returns under center for the Steelers when they face the Giants to begin a Week 1 Monday night double feature. Roethlisberger suffered a season-ending elbow injury in Week 2 and Pittsburgh struggled to an 8-8 record in 2019.

videos.title: New Orleans Saints at Las Vegas Raiders
videos.overview: The NFL opens the curtain on football in Las Vegas when the Raiders host the Saints. The Raiders surprised the Saints 35-34 in 2016 in the last meeting. Derek Carr threw a touchdown pass and a two-point conversion with 47 seconds remaining.

videos.title: Kansas City Chiefs at Baltimore Ravens
videos.overview: Lamar Jackson's Ravens host Patrick Mahomes' Chiefs in Week 3 action. The 2018 MVP outdueled the eventual 2019 MVP in a Week 3 meeting last season, with Mahomes completing 27-of-37 passes for 374 yards and three TDs in the 33-28 Kansas City triumph.

videos.title: Atlanta Falcons at Green Bay Packers
videos.overview: Aaron Rodgers' Packers host Matt Ryan's Falcons for a Week 4 clash. Green Bay ended a three-game slide against Atlanta, including a loss in the 2017 NFC Championship Game, with a 34-20 win in 2018. Julio Jones (ATL) caught two TD passes in the loss.

videos.title: Los Angeles Chargers at New Orleans Saints
videos.overview: Drew Brees aims to remain perfect in the series when his New Orleans side hosts Los Angeles. Brees defeated the Saints while with the Chargers in 2004. The 41-year-old quarterback has beaten the Chargers thrice since signing with the Saints in 2006.

videos.title: Arizona Cardinals at Dallas Cowboys
videos.overview: From AT&T Stadium in Arlington, Texas.

videos.title: Chicago Bears at Los Angeles Rams
videos.overview: The Bears and Rams meet for the third straight season in a defensive-minded series of late. Los Angeles prevailed 17-7 in 2019 after Chicago won 15-6 in 2018. The Rams' Jared Goff didn't throw a TD pass and was intercepted five times in those games.

videos.title: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New York Giants
videos.overview: With host Suzy Kolber and analysts Booger McFarland, Randy Moss and Steve Young. The crew reviews Sunday's games and looks ahead to the MNF matchup while updating fans on the latest league news.

videos.title: New England Patriots at New York Jets
videos.overview: The Patriots try for their ninth straight victory and 17th in the last 19th meetings over the Jets. New York last defeated New England 26-20 in overtime in 2015. Patriots quarterback Cam Newton was 2-0 versus the Jets while with the Panthers.

videos.title: Minnesota Vikings at Chicago Bears
videos.overview: An NFC North clash of cold-weather rivals hits Monday Night Football as the Bears play host to the Vikings. Chicago has swept the last two season series with Minnesota, holding the Vikings to just 13.75 points per game over those four victories.

videos.title: Los Angeles Rams at Tampa Bay Buccaneers
videos.overview: Tom Brady and the Buccaneers meet with Jared Goff and the Rams on Monday Night Football. Tampa Bay put up 55 points in a 2019 meeting with Los Angeles to hand the Rams their first loss of that season. The Rams are 2-3 on the road this campaign.

videos.title: Seattle Seahawks at Philadelphia Eagles
videos.overview: The Seahawks face off against the Eagles in a rematch from last season's wild-card round. DK Metcalf exploded in that game for Seattle, taking in seven catches for 160 yards and a touchdown as Seattle dispatched Philadelphia with a 17-9 victory.

videos.title: Buffalo Bills at San Francisco 49ers
videos.overview: Josh Allen and the Bills travel cross-country for a Monday night showdown with the 49ers. Allen is set to play his first NFL game in his home state, as the Firebaugh, Calif., native failed to claim victory here during his college career at Wyoming.

videos.title: Baltimore Ravens at Cleveland Browns
videos.overview: The Ravens try for a season sweep of the Browns. Baltimore beat Cleveland 38-6 in Week 1. Lamar Jackson tossed three TD passes in the win. The Browns are 5-1 at home in 2020, winning their last two at FirstEnergy Stadium by a combined eight points.

videos.title: Pittsburgh Steelers at Cincinnati Bengals
videos.overview: The Steelers seek their 12th straight victory over the Bengals. Pittsburgh prevailed 36-10 in Week 10. Ben Roethlisberger passed for 333 yards and four TDs, two to Chase Claypool, in the win. Cincinnati last defeated Pittsburgh on Nov. 1, 2015.

videos.title: Buffalo Bills at New England Patriots
videos.overview: The Bills seek their first season-series sweep of the Patriots since 1999. Buffalo's 24-21 win Nov. 1 was its first over New England since 2016. The Pats were driving to tie, but Cam Newton (NE) fumbled and lost the ball with 37 seconds left.

videos.title: Baltimore Ravens at Las Vegas Raiders
videos.overview: The Raiders begin their second campaign in Las Vegas as they host the Ravens in this season opener. If Las Vegas defensive end Carl Nassib sees action, he will become the first openly gay athlete to take part in an NFL regular-season contest.

videos.title: Detroit Lions at Green Bay Packers
videos.overview: The Packers open up Lambeau Field by hosting the Lions on Monday Night Football. Aaron Rodgers was pulled from Green Bay's blowout loss to New Orleans in Week 1 after throwing a pair of interceptions. Detroit has dropped four straight to Green Bay.

videos.title: Philadelphia Eagles at Dallas Cowboys
videos.overview: The Eagles visit the Cowboys. The two NFC East rivals split the 2020 season set, with Dallas winning a crucial Week 16 tilt at Cowboy Stadium. Michael Gallup (DAL), currently nursing a quad injury, totaled 121 receiving yards and two TDs in that win.

videos.title: Las Vegas Raiders at Los Angeles Chargers
videos.overview: Las Vegas faces Los Angeles on Monday Night Football. The Raiders find themselves at 3-0 for the first time since 2002 after surviving the Dolphins 31-28 in overtime in Week 3. Justin Herbert had four TD passes in the Chargers' upset of the Chiefs.

videos.title: Indianapolis Colts at Baltimore Ravens
videos.overview: The Colts return to their old haunts for the 10th time to collide with the Ravens. Indianapolis has lost two straight and is 4-5 in Baltimore. The franchise left the Eastern Seaboard for their new Midwest digs in the middle of a 1984 night.

videos.title: Buffalo Bills at Tennessee Titans
videos.overview: AFC contenders collide as the Titans (3-2) welcome the red-hot Bills (4-1) to the Music City. Buffalo won at Kansas City 38-20 in Week 5, and has totaled 156 points during a four-game win streak. Tennessee got back on track by beating Jacksonville.

videos.title: New Orleans Saints at Seattle Seahawks
New York Giants at Kansas City Chiefs
videos.overview: The Giants visit the defending AFC champion Chiefs. New York leads the series 11-3 after a 12-9 overtime triumph in the cold and wind in 2017. Kansas City's Travis Kelce and Tyreek Hill combined for 15 catches and 177 receiving yards in that game.

videos.title: Chicago Bears at Pittsburgh Steelers
videos.overview: The Steelers host the Bears. Pittsburgh has won three straight. Chicago's Justin Fields passed for 175 yards, rushed for 103, and accounted for two TDs in a loss to San Francisco in Week 8. Pittsburgh dealt Melvin Ingram to Kansas City on Nov. 2.

videos.title: Los Angeles Rams at San Francisco 49ers
New York Giants at Tampa Bay Buccaneers
videos.overview: Tom Brady and the Buccaneers (6-3) host the Giants (3-6). Tampa Bay has lost two straight. Brady is 5-3 versus New York after a 25-23 triumph in 2020. The future Hall of Famer is 7-3 in Super Bowls with two of the losses against the Giants.

videos.title: Seattle Seahawks at Washington Football Team
videos.overview: Seattle and Washington collide on Monday Night Football. Russell Wilson has been held without a TD pass in two straight games for the first time since 2016. The Football Team have won back-to-back games following a 27-21 win over Carolina.

videos.title: New England Patriots at Buffalo Bills
Los Angeles Rams at Arizona Cardinals
Minnesota Vikings at Chicago Bears
Miami Dolphins at New Orleans Saints
videos.overview: The Dolphins look to stay in the hunt for a playoff spot when they face the Saints in New Orleans. The Saints have won three straight in the series, including a 20-0 shutout in the most recent meeting in 2017. The overall series is tied 6-6.

videos.title: Cleveland Browns at Pittsburgh Steelers
videos.overview: The Steelers try for a season sweep of the Browns. Pittsburgh prevailed 15-10 in Week 8 to snap a two-game series slide. The Steelers' Ben Roethlisberger tossed a 2-yard TD pass to rookie Pat Freiermuth to complete the scoring with 11:04 remaining.

videos.title: Kansas City Chiefs at Denver Broncos
videos.overview: The Chiefs try to continue their mastery of the Broncos. Kansas City has won 12 straight meetings. Denver last defeated Kansas City in 2015 en route to winning the Super Bowl. The Chiefs beat the Broncos 22-9 in Week 13. Denver is 4-4 at home.

videos.title: Dallas Cowboys at Philadelphia Eagles
videos.overview: The Cowboys aim to wrap up a successful regular season as they visit the rival Eagles. Dallas raced to a 41-21 win over Philadelphia in Week 3. Cowboys quarterback Dak Prescott threw for three touchdowns, with two going to tight end Dalton Schultz.

Las Vegas Raiders at Kansas City Chiefs
Denver Broncos at Los Angeles Chargers
Chicago Bears at New England Patriots
videos.overview: The Patriots (3-3) have a potential quarterback controversy as they host the Bears (2-4). Mac Jones (ankle) has missed the last three games. Third-string rookie Bailey Zappe started, and won, the past two contests. Chicago has dropped three straight.

Los Angeles Chargers at Indianapolis Colts
videos.overview: The Chargers (8-6) attempt to strengthen their playoff position as they visit the Colts (4-9-1). Indianapolis was on the wrong end of the greatest comeback in NFL history, blowing a 33-point lead in a 39-36 overtime loss at Minnesota in Week 15.

Buffalo Bills at New York Jets

videos.overview: From The Bank of America Stadium in Charlotte, North Carolina.

videos.overview: From Paycor Stadium in Cincinnati, Ohio.

videos.title: Seattle Seahawks at New York Giants
videos.overview: From MetLife Stadium in East Rutherford, New Jersey.The Giants (1-2) hope to have Saquon Barkley back when they play the Seahawks (2-1). On Sept. 30, Barkley was officially listed as a game-time decision for this contest as he continues to work his way back from a high-ankle sprain suffered in Week 2.

videos.title: Green Bay Packers at Las Vegas Raiders
videos.overview: From Allegiant Stadium in Paradise, Nevada.The Packers (2-2) visit Sin City to face the Raiders (1-3) on Monday Night Football. Green Bay linebacker Quay Walker racked up a stunning 19 combined tackles, but his ill-timed penalty allowed Detroit to ice a 34-20 prime-time victory in Week 4.

videos.title: Dallas Cowboys at Los Angeles Chargers
videos.overview: The Chargers return from their bye to play the Cowboys on Monday Night Football. Dallas fell to 3-2 on the year with a prime-time loss at San Francisco. Los Angeles disposed of cornerback J.C. Jackson in a trade with New England during its week off.

videos.title: San Francisco 49ers at Minnesota Vikings
videos.overview: The 49ers get hyped for a third prime-time showing in five weeks when they kick off against the Vikings. San Francisco beat Minnesota 27-10 in the 2019 postseason en route to a Super Bowl appearance and followed that up with a 34-26 triumph in 2021.

videos.title: Las Vegas Raiders at Detroit Lions
Los Angeles Chargers at New York Jets
videos.overview: The streaking Jets (4-3) welcome the Chargers (3-4) to MetLife Stadium for Monday Night Football. The Jets have won three straight following a 13-10 victory in overtime over the Giants. Los Angeles is back on track after blasting Chicago 30-13.

videos.title: Denver Broncos at Buffalo Bills
Philadelphia Eagles at Kansas City Chiefs
videos.overview: The Eagles (8-1) fly into Arrowhead Stadium to take on the Chiefs (7-2) in a Super Bowl 57 rematch. Both teams were off last week. Patrick Mahomes rallied Kansas City to a 38-35 victory over Philadelphia en route to winning his second Super Bowl MVP.

videos.title: Chicago Bears at Minnesota Vikings
videos.overview: The Vikings (6-5) try to bounce back against the Bears (3-8) on Monday Night Football. Minnesota's five-game win streak came to an end in Denver last week. That run of success started with its fifth victory in a row over Chicago, 19-13 in Week 6.Add to my shows

videos.title: Cincinnati Bengals at Jacksonville Jaguars
videos.overview: The AFC South-leading Jaguars (8-3) host the sliding Bengals (5-6). Jacksonville took a two-game division lead with a 24-21 triumph at upstart Houston in Week 12. Cincinnati has lost three straight as it continues life without quarterback Joe Burrow.

videos.title: Tennessee Titans at Miami Dolphins
videos.overview: The Titans (4-8) visit the Dolphins (9-3). In Week 13, Tennessee let a late lead in overtime slip away as it fell 31-28 to division foe Indianapolis. Miami, the AFC's highest-scoring offense, flexed its muscle with a 45-15 decision over Washington.

videos.title: Philadelphia Eagles at Seattle Seahawks
videos.overview: The Eagles (10-3) and the Seahawks (6-7) try to halt their slides as they close out the Week 15 slate. Philadelphia has been outscored 75-32 in dropping its last two contests. Seattle has lost four in a row to fall into the NFC wild-card race.

videos.title: Detroit Lions at Dallas Cowboys
videos.overview: AT&T Stadium hosts a Saturday night showdown in the NFC playoff race between the Cowboys and Lions. Dallas aims to complete a perfect season at home, boasting a 7-0 mark entering this match. Detroit aims to end a five-game slide against Dallas.

videos.title: New York Jets at San Francisco 49ers
videos.overview: Aaron Rodgers and the Jets will kick off their season on Monday Night Football for the second year in a row.Rodgers heads to Northern California to play against his hometown team for the first time since 2021, when he was a member of the Packers.

videos.title: Atlanta Falcons at Philadelphia Eagles
videos.overview: The Eagles are 11-6 on Monday Night Football in the past ten years  the second most wins of any team.Kirk Cousins will make his Monday Night Football debut as a member of the Falcons.

videos.title: Jacksonville Jaguars at Buffalo Bills
videos.overview: Buffalo will host a Monday Night Football game for the fourth consecutive season.Through the first seven Monday Night Football starts of his career; Bills quarterback Josh Allen has 18 passing touchdowns, third behind only Hall of Famer Dan Marino and Mahomes who both have 19 in the same time period.

videos.title: Tennessee Titans at Miami Dolphins
videos.overview: Miami will host Tennessee on Monday Night Football for the second year in a row; last season, the Titans recorded an improbable rally in the final three minutes of the fourth quarter to beat the Dolphins (28-27).

videos.title: New Orleans Saints at Kansas City Chiefs
videos.overview: Through seven Monday Night Football starts, Kansas City quarterback Patrick Mahomes has 19 touchdown passes  tied for the most with Dan Marino in the same time period.

videos.title: Buffalo Bills at New York Jets
videos.overview: The AFC East rivals will play on Monday Night Football for the second year in a row following their highly anticipated Week 1 matchup in 2023.

videos.title: Baltimore Ravens at Tampa Bay Buccaneers
videos.overview: The reigning league MVP, Lamar Jackson, will take on the NFC South Champion Buccaneers for the second time in his career on Monday Night Football  the Ravens won the teams' first meeting, 27-22, in 2022.

videos.title: New York Giants at Pittsburgh Steelers
videos.overview: The Steelers are 13-1 on MNF in the past ten years  the most wins of any team.The last meeting between the New York Giants and the Steelers occurred on MNF in 2020 when the Steelers beat the Giants (26-16).

videos.title: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Kansas City Chiefs
videos.overview: Tampa Bay's Baker Mayfield will look for his first career win against Kansas City; in his previous starts against the Chiefs (both with Cleveland), Mayfield has a 71.43 completion percentage  his highest against any team.

videos.title: Miami Dolphins at Los Angeles Rams
videos.overview: After winning Super Bowl LVI with the Los Angeles Rams, Miami's Jalen Ramsey and Odell Beckham Jr. return to Southern California for the first time to play the Rams.

videos.title: Houston Texans at Dallas Cowboys
videos.overview: Houston wide receiver Stefon Diggs will take on his younger brother, Dallas cornerback Trevon Diggs, for the first time in their NFL careers  both as active roster members.

videos.title: Baltimore Ravens at Los Angeles Chargers
videos.overview: Ravens' head coach John Harbaugh will take on his brother, Chargers' head coach, Jim Harbaugh, in the third edition of the Harbaugh Bowl. John and the Ravens are 2-0 against Jim with the second win coming in Super Bowl XLVII.

videos.title: Cleveland Browns at Denver Broncos
videos.overview: Denver will host their first Monday Night Football game since the 2021 season.

videos.title: Cincinnati Bengals at Dallas Cowboys
videos.overview: Desperate teams come together in Big D as the Cowboys (5-7) host the Bengals (4-8). Dallas won its last two games to remain in the NFC playoff conversation. Cincinnati has plummeted down the AFC wild-card standings with three straight losses.

videos.title: Atlanta Falcons at Las Vegas Raiders
videos.overview: The Raiders will host a Monday Night Football game for the seventh year in a row.

videos.title: New Orleans Saints at Green Bay Packers
videos.overview: The Packers will appear on Monday Night Football for the 32nd consecutive season  the longest current streak among all NFL teams.

videos.title: Detroit Lions at San Francisco 49ers
videos.overview: The 49ers and Lions meet in a rematch of the 2023-24 NFC championship game, won by San Francisco 34-31. Detroit is vying for the NFC North title and the No. 1 seed in the playoffs. Entering Week 17, the Lions led the NFL with 32.9 points per outing.
